{"action": "input", "code": "def draw_green_lines(input_grid: np.ndarray, locs: List[Tuple[int, int]]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid and a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all the teal pixels in the grid,\n    draws green lines between the teal pixels which are in the same row or same column.\n    \n    Args:\n    - input_grid: a 2D numpy array representing the input grid\n    - locs: a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all the teal pixels in the grid\n    \n    Returns:\n    - A 2D numpy array representing the output grid with green lines drawn between the teal pixels which are in the same row or same column.\n    \"\"\"\n    out_grid = np.copy(input_grid)\n    for i in range(len(locs)):\n        for j in range(i + 1, len(locs)):\n            if locs[i][0] == locs[j][0] or locs[i][1] == locs[j][1]:\n                out_grid[min(locs[i][0], locs[j][0]):max(locs[i][0], locs[j][0]) + 1, min(locs[i][1], locs[j][1]):max(locs[i][1], locs[j][1]) + 1] = green\n    return out_grid\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    locs = find_teal_pixels(input_grid)\n    out_grid = draw_green_lines(input_grid, locs)\n    return out_grid\ndef find_teal_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid, returns a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all the teal pixels in the grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    - input_grid: a 2D numpy array representing the input grid\n    \n    Returns:\n    - A list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all the teal pixels in the grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    teal_pixels = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == teal:\n                teal_pixels.append((i, j))\n    return teal_pixels", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n  locs = `find the location of teal pixels`(input_grid)\n  out_grid = `draw green lines between the teal pixels which are in the same row or same column`(input_grid, locs)\n  return out_grid", "gpt_code": "def draw_green_lines(input_grid: np.ndarray, locs: List[Tuple[int, int]]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid and a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all the teal pixels in the grid,\n    draws green lines between the teal pixels which are in the same row or same column.\n    \n    Args:\n    - input_grid: a 2D numpy array representing the input grid\n    - locs: a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all the teal pixels in the grid\n    \n    Returns:\n    - A 2D numpy array representing the output grid with green lines drawn between the teal pixels which are in the same row or same column.\n    \"\"\"\n    out_grid = np.copy(input_grid)\n    for i in range(len(locs)):\n        for j in range(i + 1, len(locs)):\n            if locs[i][0] == locs[j][0] or locs[i][1] == locs[j][1]:\n                out_grid[min(locs[i][0], locs[j][0]):max(locs[i][0], locs[j][0]) + 1, min(locs[i][1], locs[j][1]):max(locs[i][1], locs[j][1]) + 1] = green\n    return out_grid\ndef find_teal_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid, returns a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all the teal pixels in the grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    - input_grid: a 2D numpy array representing the input grid\n    \n    Returns:\n    - A list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all the teal pixels in the grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    teal_pixels = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == teal:\n                teal_pixels.append((i, j))\n    return teal_pixels", "holes": {"draw_green_lines": "draw green lines between the teal pixels which are in the same row or same column", "find_teal_pixels": "find the location of teal pixels"}}
