{"action": "edit", "code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    locs = find_teal_pixels(input_grid)\n    out_grid = change_pixels_to_green_between_teal_pixels_in_same_row(input_grid, locs)\n    out_grid = change_pixels_to_green_between_teal_pixels_in_same_column(out_grid, locs)\n    return out_grid\ndef change_pixels_to_green_between_teal_pixels_in_same_row(input_grid: np.ndarray, teal_pixels: List[Tuple[int, int]]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid and a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all teal pixels in the grid,\n    changes the pixels to green between the teal pixels which are in the same row.\n    \n    Args:\n    - input_grid (np.ndarray): A 2D numpy array representing the input grid.\n    - teal_pixels (List[Tuple[int, int]]): A list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all teal pixels in the grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    - np.ndarray: A 2D numpy array representing the output grid with pixels changed to green between the teal pixels which are in the same row.\n    \"\"\"\n    out_grid = input_grid.copy()\n    for i, j in teal_pixels:\n        row = out_grid[i]\n        left = j\n        right = j\n        while left > 0 and row[left - 1] != teal:\n            left -= 1\n        while right < len(row) - 1 and row[right + 1] != teal:\n            right += 1\n        for k in range(left, right + 1):\n            row[k] = green\n    return out_grid\ndef find_teal_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid, returns a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all teal pixels in the grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    - input_grid (np.ndarray): A 2D numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    - List[Tuple[int, int]]: A list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all teal pixels in the grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    teal_pixels = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == teal:\n                teal_pixels.append((i, j))\n    return teal_pixels\ndef change_pixels_to_green_between_teal_pixels_in_same_column(input_grid: np.ndarray, teal_pixels: List[Tuple[int, int]]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid and a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all teal pixels in the grid,\n    changes the pixels to green between the teal pixels which are in the same column.\n    \n    Args:\n    - input_grid (np.ndarray): A 2D numpy array representing the input grid.\n    - teal_pixels (List[Tuple[int, int]]): A list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all teal pixels in the grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    - np.ndarray: A 2D numpy array representing the output grid with pixels changed to green between the teal pixels which are in the same column.\n    \"\"\"\n    out_grid = input_grid.copy()\n    for i, j in teal_pixels:\n        col = out_grid[:, j]\n        top = i\n        bottom = i\n        while top > 0 and col[top - 1] != teal:\n            top -= 1\n        while bottom < len(col) - 1 and col[bottom + 1] != teal:\n            bottom += 1\n        for k in range(top, bottom + 1):\n            out_grid[k][j] = green\n    return out_grid", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n  locs = `find the location of teal pixels`(input_grid)\n  out_grid = `change the pixels to green between the teal pixels which are in the same row`(input_grid, locs)\n  out_grid = `change the pixels to green between the teal pixels which are in the same column`(out_grid, locs)\n  return out_grid", "gpt_code": "def change_pixels_to_green_between_teal_pixels_in_same_row(input_grid: np.ndarray, teal_pixels: List[Tuple[int, int]]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid and a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all teal pixels in the grid,\n    changes the pixels to green between the teal pixels which are in the same row.\n